Combine dried sage, salt, and black pepper; sprinkle over pork. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat. Add pork; cook 3 minutes on each side or until done. Remove pork from pan; cover and keep warm. Melt butter in pan over medium heat. Add apples and next 4 ingredients; cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently. Serve apple mixture with pork chops.